base5.flavorText: Freezes its prey with its stare. If you should encounter one, remember not to look into its eyes.

base5.name: Dark Blastoise

attacks.name: Continuous Fireball

base5.flavorText: Seemingly possessed, it spews fire like a volcano, trying to burn all it sees.

attacks.name: Giant Tail
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

base5.flavorText: Sometimes called "The God of Destruction." Its wings are able to support it in spite of its massive weight.

base5.name: Dark Dugtrio

abilities.name: Sinkhole
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent's Active Pokémon retreats, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this power does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power stops working while Dark Dugtrio is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Knock Down
attacks.text: Your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage; if heads, this attack does 20 damage.

base5.flavorText: Digs large sinkholes in the ground and tries to trap its enemies in them.

base5.name: Dark Golbat

abilities.name: Sneak Attack
abilities.text: When you play Dark Golbat from your hand, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If you do, Dark Golbat does 10 damage to that Pokémon. Apply Weakness and Resistance.

attacks.name: Flitter

base5.flavorText: Sneaks up silently on its prey and attacks it from behind, sometimes killing it with one bite.

base5.name: Dark Gyarados

abilities.name: Final Beam
abilities.text: When Dark Gyarados is Knocked Out by an attack, flip a coin. attacks.name: Ice Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

base5.flavorText: Normally found only in the deep ocean, it has recently been seen in shallow waters as well.

base5.name: Dark Hypno

attacks.name: Bench Manipulation
attacks.text: Your opponent flips a number of coins equal to the number of Pokémon on his or her Bench. This attack does 20 damage times the number of tails. base5.flavorText: Carries a pendulum with it always. Sometimes appears near less-traveled roads and schools at dusk.

attacks.name: Fling
attacks.text: Your opponent shuffles his or her Active Pokémon and all cards attached to it into his or her deck. This attack can't be used if your opponent has no Benched Pokémon.

base5.flavorText: It is almost impossible to defend against a Machamp's four powerful arms.

base1.flavorText: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

base1.name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Bubblebeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

base1.flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

base1.name: Hitmonchan
base1.flavorText: While seeming to do nothing, it fires punches in lightning-fast volleys that are impossible to see.

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Barrier

dp1.flavorText: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy attached to Electivire. If you do, this attack's base damage is 120 instead of 60.

dp1.flavorText: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Flare Blitz

dp1.flavorText: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.

dp1.name: Lucario

attacks.name: Feint
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Aura Sphere
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

dp1.flavorText: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

abilities.name: Gleam Eyes
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play Luxray from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may look at your opponent's hand. attacks.name: Lightning Star
attacks.text: Move all Lightning Energy attached to Luxray to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Ignore this effect if you don't have any Benched Pokémon.)

dp1.flavorText: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.

dp1.flavorText: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

attacks.name: Aqua Ring
attacks.text: Switch Manaphy with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

dp1.flavorText: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

dp1.name: Mismagius

attacks.name: Avenge
attacks.text: Count the number of your Pokémon that have any damage counters on them. Put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psywave
attacks.text: Does 30 damage plus 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

dp1.flavorText: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

si1.flavorText: This Pokémon's body is covered by fine hairs that can be seen only under a microscope.

si1.name: Pidgeot

attacks.name: Supersonic Flight
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

si1.flavorText: This Pokémon searches for food while flying at Mach 2. Its large claws make fearsome weapons.

attacks.name: Slam

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Bawl
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

si1.flavorText: A sure sign spring is on its way is when the seed on this Pokémon's back flowers.

attacks.name: Sharp Teeth

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Ledyba.

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

si1.flavorText: After lulling its enemies with its large eyes, this Pokémon sings them to sleep with a relaxing melody.

attacks.name: Fly
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Butterfree. If tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

si1.name: Tentacruel

attacks.name: Tentacle Grip
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Water Energy attached to Tentacruel. For each heads, draw 2 cards.

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

si1.flavorText: This Pokémon attacks its prey with its eighty toxin-producing tentacles.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

abilities.name: Wave Veil

attacks.name: Line Force
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

attacks.text: If any of your Benched Magmortar have any damage counters on them, this attack does 90 more damage.

attacks.name: Heat Tackle

attacks.name: Growl

swsh11tg.flavorText: Mushroom-lacking specimens of this Pokémon lie unmoving in the forest, lending credence to the hypothesis that the large mushroom is in control of Parasect's actions.

attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

swsh11tg.flavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

swsh11tg.name: Charizard

attacks.name: Royal Blaze

swsh11tg.flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

swsh11tg.name: Chandelure

abilities.name: Mountain Roasting
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

swsh11tg.flavorText: This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.

swsh11tg.name: Pikachu

abilities.name: Pika Dash
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

attacks.name: Whimsy Tackle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

swsh11tg.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

swsh11tg.name: Gengar

abilities.name: Netherworld Gate
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in your discard pile, you may put it onto your Bench. If you do, put 3 damage counters on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Screaming Circle
attacks.text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

swsh11tg.flavorText: Possesses potential victims' shadows in an effort to steal away the victims' lives. If your shadow begins to laugh, you must take hold of a protective charm posthaste!

swsh11tg.name: Banette

attacks.name: Resolute Spite
attacks.text: Put up to 7 damage counters on this Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter you placed in this way.

attacks.name: Eerie Light
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

swsh11tg.flavorText: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.

swsh11tg.name: Hisuian Arcanine

attacks.name: Very Vulnerable
attacks.text: If you have no cards in your hand, this attack does 150 more damage.

swsh11tg.flavorText: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.

swsh11tg.name: Spiritomb

abilities.name: Cursed Message
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Chain of Spirits
attacks.text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Spiritomb in your discard pile.

swsh11tg.flavorText: It lays curses by thinking wicked thoughts. Writings tell that this Pokémon was born out of the assembly of five score and eight malevolent spirits.

swsh11tg.name: Snorlax

abilities.name: Unfazed Fat
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon. (Damage is not an effect.)

attacks.name: Thumping Snore

swsh11tg.flavorText: This glutton appears in villages without warning and devours the entirety of their rice granaries—such occurrences have long been counted among the gravest of disasters.

sm7.name: Bellsprout

attacks.name: Blot
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

sm7.flavorText: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

sm7.name: Weepinbell

attacks.name: Double Razor Leaf
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

sm7.flavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

sm7.name: Victreebel

abilities.name: Fragrance Trap
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Corrosive Acid
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

sm7.flavorText: Once ingested into this Pokémon's body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

sm7.name: Scyther

attacks.name: Twin Play
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Scyther and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

sm7.flavorText: While young, they live together deep in the mountains, training themselves in how to fight with their scythes and move at high speeds.

sm7.name: Spinarak

attacks.name: Stun Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

sm7.flavorText: Some fishermen weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokémon.

sm7.name: Ariados

attacks.name: Reactive Poison
attacks.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spider Trap
attacks.text: You may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

sm7.flavorText: It spins thread from both its rear and its mouth. Then it wraps its prey up in thread and sips their bodily fluids at its leisure.

sm7.name: Treecko

attacks.name: Sleep Poison
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

sm7.flavorText: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

sm7.name: Treecko

sm7.name: Grovyle

attacks.name: Leaf Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

sm7.flavorText: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

sm7.name: Sceptile

attacks.name: Powerful Storm
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

sm7.flavorText: It agilely leaps about the jungle and uses the sharp leaves on its arms to strike its prey.

hgss3.name: Bellossom

abilities.name: Hustle Step
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Bellossom is affected by a Special Condition.

hgss3.name: Espeon

attacks.name: Mirror Shot
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

hgss3.flavorText: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.

hgss3.name: Gliscor

attacks.name: Ninja Fang
attacks.text: If, before Gliscor does damage, the Defending Pokémon has no damage counters on it and is then damaged by this attack (after applying Weakness and Resistance), the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Poison Jab
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

hgss3.name: Houndoom

attacks.name: Fire Counterattack

attacks.name: Dark Roar

hgss3.flavorText: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

hgss3.name: Magcargo

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Lava Flow
attacks.text: You may discard any number of Fire Energy cards attached to Magcargo. If you do , this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage for each Fire Energy card you discarded.

hgss3.flavorText: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.

hgss3.name: Scizor
hgss3.flavorText: Its wings are not used for flying. They are flapped at high speed to adjust its body temperature.

hgss3.name: Smeargle

abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Smeargle is your Active Pokémon, you may look at your opponent's hand. attacks.name: Tail Rap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.text: Remove all damage counters from each of your Pokémon. Shuffle Togekiss and all cards attached to it back into your deck.

attacks.name: Air Cutter
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

swsh8.name: Caterpie

swsh8.name: Butterfree

swsh8.name: Shroomish
swsh8.flavorText: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

swsh8.name: Breloom V

swsh8.name: Breloom

attacks.name: Impact Blow
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Impact Blow.

swsh8.flavorText: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

swsh8.name: Pansage
swsh8.flavorText: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

swsh8.name: Simisage

attacks.name: Return
attacks.text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

swsh8.flavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

swsh8.name: Sewaddle

attacks.name: Grass Munch
attacks.text: Discard a Grass Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

swsh8.flavorText: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

swsh8.name: Swadloon

attacks.name: Trip Over

attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy attached to Garchomp and this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

pop9.flavorText: It flies at speeds equal to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.

attacks.name: Dive

attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Remove from Manaphy the number of damage counters equal to the damage you did to that Pokémon.

pop9.flavorText: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

pop9.name: Raichu

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: High Volt
attacks.text: If Raichu evolved from Pikachu during this turn, this attack's base damage is 100 instead of 60.

pop9.flavorText: It can loose 100,000-volt bursts of electricity, instantly downing foes several times its size.

pop9.name: Regigigas

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Double Stomp
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Poltergeist

pop9.flavorText: Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

pop9.name: Buizel

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Super Fast
attacks.text: If you have Pachirisu in play, flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Buizel during your opponent's next turn.

pop9.flavorText: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

pop9.name: Croagunk

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

attacks.name: Nimble
attacks.text: If you have Turtwig in play, remove from Croagunk the number of damage counters equal to the damage you did to the Defending Pokémon.

pop9.flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it makes an eerie blubbering sound for intimidation.

pop9.name: Gabite

attacks.name: Burrow
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Gabite by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Distored Wave
attacks.text: Before doing damage, remove 2 damage counters from the Defending Pokémon.

pop9.flavorText: It habitually digs up and hoards gems in its nest. Its loot is constantly targeted by thieves.

pop9.name: Lopunny

attacks.name: Jump Kick
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Jazzed
attacks.text: If Lopunny evolved from Buneary during this turn, remove all damage counters from Lopunny.

pop9.flavorText: It is very conscious of its looks and never fails to groom its ears. It runs with sprightly jumps.

pop9.name: Pachirisu

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Poison Berry

attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. Metronome copies that attack except for its Energy costs and anything else required in order to use that attack, such as discarding Energy cards. (No matter what type the Defending Pokémon is, Clefairy's type is still Colorless.)

base4.flavorText: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

base4.name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Bubblebeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

base4.flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

base4.name: Hitmonchan
base4.flavorText: While seeming to do nothing, it fires punches in lightning-fast volleys that are impossible to see.

base4.name: Magneton

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Selfdestruct
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to each player's Bench. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Magneton does 80 damage to itself.

base4.flavorText: Formed by several Magnemites linked together. It frequently appears when sunspots flare up.

base4.name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Barrier
attacks.text: Discard 1 Psychic Energy card attached to Mewtwo in order to use this attack. During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Mewtwo.

base4.flavorText: A scientist created this Pokémon after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

sv2.name: Hoppip

attacks.name: Splashing Dodge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

sv2.flavorText: This Pokémon is blown across vast distances by the wind. It is unclear where the Hoppip of Paldea originally came from.

sv2.name: Skiploom

abilities.name: Drifting Dodge
abilities.text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

attacks.name: Flowery Zephyr
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

sv2.flavorText: Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the flower on the Pokémon's head.

sv2.name: Pineco
sv2.flavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

sv2.name: Jumpluff

abilities.name: Drifting Dodge
abilities.text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

attacks.name: Fluffy Breeze
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

sv2.flavorText: Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its cotton spores run out, its journey ends, as does its life.

sv2.name: Tropius

attacks.name: Leaf Drain
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Tropic Breeze
attacks.text: Move all Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

sv2.flavorText: It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows twice a year.

sv2.name: Forretress ex
rules: Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Exploding Energy
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 5 Basic Grass Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. If you searched your deck in this way, this Pokémon is Knocked Out.

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

sv2.name: Heracross

attacks.name: Smashing Horn
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

sv2.flavorText: It loves sweet nectar. To keep all the nectar to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.

sv2.name: Sprigatito

attacks.name: Gather Sunlight
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

sv2.flavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

sv2.name: Sprigatito
sv2.flavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

sv2.name: Floragato

attacks.name: Magic Whip
attacks.text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

sv2.flavorText: Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.

sm1.name: Caterpie

attacks.name: Nap
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

sm1.flavorText: When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.

sm1.name: Metapod

attacks.name: Iron Defense
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

sm1.flavorText: Its shell is filled with its soft innards. It doesn't move much because of the risk it might carelessly spill its innards out.

sm1.name: Butterfree

attacks.name: Psy Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

sm1.flavorText: Close examination of its large eyes reveals that each eye is composed of a myriad of tiny eyes.

sm1.name: Paras
sm1.flavorText: No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.

sm1.name: Parasect

attacks.name: Fury Cutter
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. If 1 of them is heads, this attack does 20 more damage. If 2 of them are heads, this attack does 60 more damage. If all of them are heads, this attack does 120 damage.

attacks.name: Mushroom Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

sm1.flavorText: The large mushroom on its back controls it. It often fights over territory with Shiinotic.

sm1.name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Roof Fling
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, put your opponent's Active Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your opponent's hand.

sm1.flavorText: One solid blow from its horns is enough to split apart a large tree. Its greatest rival in Alola is Vikavolt.

sm1.name: Surskit

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

sm1.flavorText: When this Pokémon senses danger, a sweet fluid oozes from the tip of its heads. The taste of it disgusts bird Pokémon.

sm1.name: Masquerain

attacks.name: Struggle Bug
attacks.text: Move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

sm1.flavorText: Its wings and antennae don't cope well with moisture. After a rain, it faces sunward to dry off.

sm1.name: Rowlet
sm1.flavorText: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

sm1.name: Dartrix

attacks.name: Sharp Blade Quill
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Leaf Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

sm1.flavorText: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

attacks.name: Splashing Dodge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

abilities.name: Compound Eyes
abilities.text: Attacks used by this Pokémon do 50 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon that has an Ability (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Shocking Web
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Lightning Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

attacks.name: Add On
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: United Wings
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the United Wings attack.

attacks.name: Stock Up on Feathers
attacks.text: Draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Power Shot
attacks.text: Discard a Basic Grass Energy card from your hand. If you can't, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Wood Hammer
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Snarl
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do 100 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Suction
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Anachronism Repulsor
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Ancient Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hold Still
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

xy7.name: Oddish

attacks.name: Trip Over
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

xy7.flavorText: Its scientific name is "Oddium Wanderus." At night, it is said to walk nearly 1,000 feet on its two roots.

xy7.name: Gloom
xy7.flavorText: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

xy7.name: Vileplume

abilities.name: Irritating Pollen
abilities.text: Each player can't play any Item cards from his or her hand.

xy7.flavorText: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

xy7.name: Bellossom

attacks.name: Windmill
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Flower Tornado
attacks.text: Move as many Grass Energy attached to your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

xy7.flavorText: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

xy7.name: Spinarak

attacks.name: String Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

xy7.flavorText: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.

xy7.name: Ariados

abilities.name: Poisonous Nest
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this Ability. Both Active Pokémon (except for Grass Pokémon) are now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Impound
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

xy7.flavorText: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.

xy7.name: Sceptile-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Sleep Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Unseen Claw
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 70 more damage.

xy7.name: M Sceptile-EX
rules: Mega Evolution rule: When 1 of your Pokémon becomes a Mega Evolution Pokémon, your turn ends.
Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ancientTrait.name: θ Stop
ancientTrait.text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's Pokémon's Abilities done to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Jagged Saber
attacks.text: You may attach up to 2 Grass Energy cards from your hand to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, heal all damage from that Pokémon.

xy7.name: Combee
xy7.flavorText: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

xy7.name: Vespiquen

attacks.name: Intelligence Gathering
attacks.text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Bee Revenge
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile.

xy7.flavorText: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.

xy10.name: Shuckle

attacks.name: Hide a Berry
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards. Then, put a card from your hand on the bottom of your deck.

attacks.name: Wrap
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

xy10.flavorText: It stores Berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

xy10.name: Burmy
xy10.flavorText: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

xy10.name: Wormadam

attacks.name: Solar Ray
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Leaf Cutter
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

xy10.flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

xy10.name: Mothim

abilities.name: Wormadam First
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Wormadam to another of your Pokémon.

xy10.flavorText: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

xy10.name: Snivy

attacks.name: Blot
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

xy10.flavorText: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

xy10.name: Servine

abilities.name: Serpentine Strangle
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

xy10.flavorText: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

xy10.name: Serperior

attacks.name: Coil
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's attacks do 60 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Slashing Strike
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't use Slashing Strike during your next turn.

xy10.flavorText: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

xy10.name: Deerling

attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

xy10.flavorText: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

xy10.name: Moltres

attacks.name: Flying Flare
attacks.text: You may do 40 more damage. If you do, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

xy10.flavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

xy10.name: Fennekin

attacks.name: Tail Whip
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

xy10.flavorText: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.
